<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   SKNDF Official Supports Reunification by Confederacy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1201054294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0419 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1201054294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- Kim Kwang-chon, 
vice- chairman of the Central Committee of the South Korean 
National Democratic Front [SKNDF] (Hanminjon), issued a 
statement January 6, fully supporting the policy of reunifying 
the country by the confederacy formula on the principles of 
independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity 
reiterated by the great leader President Kim Il-song in his New 
Year address, Seoul-based radio Voice of National Salvation 
reported. 
  "No force on earth can break the will of our fellow 
countrymen to reunify the country in the 1990s no matter how 
hard the separatist forces at home and abroad may work and how 
the situation surrounding us may change, so long as the Koreans 
in the South, North and overseas are guided by the great leader 
President Kim Il-song whom they all worship and follow and the 
chuche-based principles and line of national reunification and 
the 10-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation 
light the road ahead of the nation," said the vice-chairman. 
  "Hanminjon", he declared, "will join the patriotic people of 
all walks of life in speeding up the onward movement for the 
reunification of the country that will unite the 70 million 
Koreans in one body, under the banner of the 10- point programme 
of the great unity of the whole nation uo forward by President 
Kim Il-song and contribute to making this year a year of 
national harmony and unity." 

</TEXT>

